  "text": "In some situations, heifers and cows were evaluated for the presence of CL-detectable transrectal palpation and administered 500 mg of cloprostenol intramuscularly (Ciosin; Schering-Coopers, Cotia, São Paulo, Brazil) to induce estrus. Females with well-developed CL 6 to 8 days after the onset of estrus were used as recipients. However, in most cases, a fixed-time ET protocol with progesterone and estradiol benzoate-associated prostaglandin, eCG, and estradiol cypionate was used for recipient estrus synchrony, as previously described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Without estrous detection, Day 10 was considered the day of estrus, and the embryos were transferred on Day 17. Before ET, the ovaries of each recipient were examined using ultrasonography (Aloka SSD 500 with 5-MHz linear transducer; Tokyo, Japan) to confirm the presence and size of the CL. Only recipients with a CL greater than or equal to 13 mm in diameter received an embryo.",
